1.title: Oh My Santa
1.plot: When Max gets a case of the bah-humbugs -- and Tommy has a meltdown at the mall -- DJ does everything she can to get them back in the Christmas spirit.

2.title: Big Night
2.plot: The pressure is on for DJ and Steve to have the perfect date. Stephanie puts a hold on Kimmy and Fernando from being affectionate. Jackson struggles with Rocki on whether they are boyfriend and girlfriend or not.

3.title: A Sense of Purpose
3.plot: With a baby on the way, Steph starts thinking like a provider. Danny ponders going back to work-related and Matt and DJ try to bust each other's businesses.

4.title: Ghosted
4.plot: Steve and DJ's "two-week-iversary" turns into a gift-giving competition. Steph performs at her first kids' party, and Ramona gets ghosted.

5.title: No Escape
5.plot: D.J. and Steve go on a double date with Matt and his new girlfriend. Stephanie and Kimmy host a Lamaze class at the house.

6.title: Angels' Night Out
6.plot: While Joey watches the boys at home, DJ and the girls don flashy costumes for a '70's-themed cruise. But it's not quite the crowd they expected. Fernando and Ramona spend the day together and the boys pull a prank on Joey.

7.title: President Fuller
7.plot: Max runs for fourth-grade class president - but his girlfriend Rose is running, too. DJ tries to make up with CJ, and Steph picks a fight with a clown.

8.title: Driving Mr. Jackson
8.plot: Jackson and Ramona's first high school party has major consequences, when Jackson got drunk. Becky and Jesse team up to host an awards show, where a big win goes to Matt's head.

9.title: Perfect Sons
9.plot: Fernando's mother pays a surprise visit, so he presents that he Kimberly live here, have a baby and have D.J as her maid and Steve teaches Jackson how to drive. Max makes a memorable debut on "Wake Up San Francisco" when he got a B.

10.title: Golden-Toe Fuller
10.plot: Jackson's a star football player -- but the pressure is getting to him. DJ plans a gender reveal party and Jesse tries to bond with other dads.

11.title: It's Always Open
11.plot: When DJ worries that Jimmy isn't ready for fatherhood, an angry Steph responds by joining a dodge ball team. Kimmy sets Ramona up with her new intern.

12.title: The Prom
12.plot: Prom night brings big problems for Jackson and Ramona. Meanwhile, a power-hungry DJ is taking her role as head chaperon a little too seriously. Joey and Fernando duel over a chilly cook off.

13.title: Opening Night
13.plot: While the She-wolf pack is watching Hamilton, Kimmy goes into labor.

1.title: Our Very First Show, Again
1.plot: The entire Tanner clan comes together for a final reunion before the family home is sold, but parting turns out to be tougher than expected.

2.title: Moving Day
2.plot: When the big day comes for Stephanie and Kimmy to join the Fuller house, Jackson feels outnumbered and takes drastic action.

3.title: Funner House
3.plot: When Stephanie, Kimmy and DJ have a girls' night out and leave Joey in charge of the kids, things get wild out on the town and at home.

4.title: The Not-So-Great Escape
4.plot: Ramona has Jackson trip the fire alarm at their school so she can get out of class and ditch it. The plan is successful except it results in Jackson getting punished by D.J and Ramona receiving no punishment at all.

5.title: Mad Max
5.plot: When an old friend whisks her away for a concert and after-hours fun, Stephanie realizes just how much her nephews mean to her. Kimmy finds D.J. a date.

6.title: The Legend of El Explosivo
6.plot: DJ punishes Jackson, causing him to miss his favorite Mexican wrestling league, Lucha Kaboom. But that only leads to more action for the fans.

7.title: Ramona's Not-So-Epic Party
7.plot: Kimmy and Fernando put together Ramona's much-anticipated 13th Birthday party and it doesn't go as planned, for anybody. Meanwhile Steve (out of jealousy) tries to set up DJ's attractive co-worker with Kimmy.

8.title: Secrets, Lies and Firetrucks
8.plot: When Max learns to lie, he also learns that lies can backfire. Meanwhile, the ladies of the house fall in love with secrets.

9.title: War of the Roses
9.plot: After 1,000 roses show up without a card, D.J., Kimmy, and Stephanie must figure out which one of them has a secret admirer.

10.title: A Giant Leap
10.plot: Things get out of hand when Stephanie's new boyfriend, Hunter Pence of the San Francisco Giants, invites everyone to one of his baseball games.

11.title: Partnerships in the Night
11.plot: Stephanie and Kimmy form a strange partnership, D.J.'s boss retires, and Max has Jackson and Ramona right where he wants them.

12.title: Save the Dates
12.plot: D.J. has a date with her past that catches her off guard, and Kimmy's date with Fernando is nothing but surprises.

13.title: Love Is in the Air
13.plot: When Jesse and Becky return to renew their vows, a bachelorette party leads to trouble for D.J., who is forced to make a big decision.

1.title: Welcome Back
1.plot: DJ finally decides between Matt and Steve, but they throw her a curveball before her annual back-to-school barbecue; A homeless Fernando moves in.

2.title: Mom Interference
2.plot: It's a full house for game night when Steve and Matt bring uninvited guests. Jackson decides to join the football team.

3.title: Ramona's Not-So-Epic First Kiss
3.plot: Ramona's first kiss leads to a heartbreaking lesson in love. A memorable sister night makes wedding crashers out of DJ and Stephanie

4.title: Curse of Tanner Manor
4.plot: Jackson and Ramona would rather die than go to DJs family Halloween party, where Fernando and Kimmy pull off the ultimate couples costume.

5.title: Doggy Daddy
5.plot: A not so typical day involves a dance audition, a toddler play date, four chickens, and a vet emergency. Matt comes to an important realization.

6.title: Fuller Thanksgiving
6.plot: The house feels overstuffed when the entire Tanner Family shows up for Thanksgiving, pushing DJs organizational skills into overdrive.

7.title: Girl Talk
7.plot: Kimmy hatches a plan to get the girls' childhood band, Girl Talk, back together. A vengeful video making fun of Ramona goes viral

8.title: A Tangled Web
8.plot: Jackson pet-sits Lola's tarantula, Dj works over time to help Max on a school project, and Jimmy makes a music video for Stephanie's latest hit.

9.title: Glazed and Confused
9.plot: With out-of-town trips planned for the adults, Uncle Joey delivers doughnuts -- and unexpected drama. Stephanie's nervous about singing on television.

10.title: New Kids in the House
10.plot: Kimmy and Stephanie have an epic surprise planned for DJ's 39th birthday, but things don't go as planned.

11.title: DJ and Kimmy's High School Reunion
11.plot: A high school reunion leaves DJ wondering wether she still has feelings for Steve, while a hapless Kimmy is trending for all the wrong reasons.

12.title: Nutcrackers
12.plot: 'Tis the season to be in love, but Stephanie doesn't want to hear it. Max gets a girlfriend for Christmas, and Ramona suits up for "The Nutcracker."

13.title: Happy New Year Baby
13.plot: Steve comes to DJ for help with an important proposal. Jesse and Becky's new addition brings Danny and Joey home -- and has Jimmy spouting baby talk.

1.title: Best Summer Ever
1.plot: DJ makes Jackson take summer school. Steve and CJ make a surprise announcement. Jimmy has a hard time trying to find somewhere to park his RV. Fernando is keeping a secret from Kimmy.

2.title: Break a Leg
2.plot: DJ offers herself as Stephanie's life coach while Kimmy offers herself as Steve and CJ's wedding planner...in Japan

3.title: Declarations of Independence
3.plot: The gang agrees to help Stephanie become more self sufficient and Danny Tanner shows up for the 4th of July barbecue.

4.title: My Little Hickey
4.plot: Ramona asks Stephanie to keep quiet about her hickey while Fernando has a hard time adjusting to his new living situation.

5.title: Uncle Jesse's Adventures in Babysitting
5.plot: Fernando converts Kimmy's old house into an exact replica of her childhood, which DJ, Stephanie and Kimmy visit while visiting Uncle Jesse babysits all the kids.

6.title: M-M-M-My Ramona
6.plot: When Jackson frets over a bird that flew into a window, DJ gets the feeling that there's another veterinarian in the family. Fernando and Kimmy fight over Ramona and Max freaks when Tommy destroys his stuffed unicorn.

7.title: Say Yes to the Dress
7.plot: DJ gets caught up in the moment while trying a wedding dress on while Steve gets fitted for his tux. Stephanie feels left out when she's not invited to a movie premier that features one of her songs.

8.title: Maybe Baby
8.plot: Aunt Becky shows up to spend the day with Stephanie and Joey shows up with his children, who are little terrors all over the house. DJ quizzes Jackson on History then talks to his teacher when he bombs the test.

9.title: Wedding or Not Here We Come
9.plot: The gang prepares for the trip to Japan, including DJ, who's all thumbs over her relationship status with Steve. Jimmy is left out of Stephanie's decision to have a baby while Fernando teaches Max the finer points of conning a free seat in first class.

10.title: My Best Friend's Japanese Wedding
10.plot: In Japan, Steve and CJ's wedding dishes up one disaster after another -- from a maid of honor who's MIA to a talking toilet with an alarming appetite.

11.title: Troller Coaster
11.plot: Ramona reconsiders her future, while Max tempts fate on the "Troller Coaster".

12.title: Fast Times At Bayview High
12.plot: Jimmy and Stephanie take a step toward their future, as Jackson and Ramona begin high school.

13.title: A Tommy Tale
13.plot: D.J. attempts to get Tommy into a fancy daycare.

14.title: Surrogate City
14.plot: Stephanie and Jimmy begin their search for a surrogate. Jackson's rebellion pushes all of D.J.'s buttons.

15.title: Soul Sisters
15.plot: Stephanie and Kimmy try and connect, while DJ has a "diddily" day. Max and Jackson broke a classic statue in the living room, and get Ramona to Help with repairs. Fernando buys something awesome for Tommy.

16.title: Happily Ever After
16.plot: The she-wolves come to the rescue when Ramona gets in trouble. Stephanie and Kimmy deal with a demanding client.

17.title: Fullers in a Fog
17.plot: D.J. preps for an important date, while Danny, Joey, and Jesse celebrate their 30 year "Dadiversary".

18.title: Here Comes the Sun
18.plot: The gang tries to get their magic back with an 80s themed party.

imdb.plot outline: Fuller House is a spin-off series based on the hit ABC family sitcom Full House (1987-95) created and executive produced by Jeff Franklin for Netflix. D.J. Tanner-Fuller (Candace Cameron-Bure) is a recently widowed mom to a 13-year-old named Jackson (Michael Campion), 7-year-old named Max (Elias Harger), and a newborn son named Tommy (Fox and Dashiell Messitt). After realizing she is unable to cope with the demands of holding a full time job as a veterinarian in addition to raising three kids, her sister Stephanie (Jodie Sweetin) and childhood best friend Kimmy (Andrea Barber), who is also the mother of a 13-year-old daughter (Soni Bringas), offer to move in to bring up her children.
imdb.title: Fuller House
plot: In a continuation of _Full House (1987)_ (qv), D.J. Fuller is a mother of three young boys and is a recent widow. D.J.'s sister Stephanie, her best friend Kimmy and Kimmy's teenage daughter all move in to help raise her sons. The house is now a lot fuller.::Makayla

_Fuller House_ (qv) is a spin-off series based on the hit ABC family sitcom Full House (1987-95) created and executive produced by Jeff Franklin for Netflix. D.J. Tanner-Fuller (Candace Cameron-Bure) is a recently widowed mom to a 13-year-old named Jackson (Michael Campion), 7-year-old named Max (Elias Harger), and a newborn son named Tommy (Fox and Dashiell Messitt). After realizing she is unable to cope with the demands of holding a full time job as a veterinarian in addition to raising three kids, her sister Stephanie (Jodie Sweetin) and childhood best friend Kimmy (Andrea Barber), who is also the mother of a 13-year-old daughter (Soni Bringas), offer to move in to bring up her children.::Eli Allen
